Cool to cold weather is expected on Friday, ahead of a wintery weekend. Strong interior north-westerly winds of 50-65km/h are expected in places over the interior of Northern Cape's Namakwa District, the Central Karoo, the Cape Winelands and the Little Karoo of the Western Cape on Sunday, according to the South African Weather Service. The weather in your region It will be fine and cool in Gauteng. The expected UVB sunburn index will be low. Mpumalanga will be cloudy in the east, where isolated showers are expected. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool to warm. Drizzle is expected along the escarpment. It will be partly cloudy and cool to warm in Limpopo. Isolated showers are expected in the east at first. Drizzle is expected along the escarpment. The North West will be fine and cool, but warm in the extreme north-east. It will be cloudy in the eastern parts of the Free State at first, with morning fog patches. Otherwise, it will be fine and cool. The Northern Cape will be very cold over the interior at first, with frost in places. Otherwise, it will be fine and cool, but cold over the southern interior. The wind along the coast will be moderate. It will be very cold at first over the interior of the Western Cape, with frost in places. Otherwise, it will be fine and cool, becoming cloudy along the southern parts of the West Coast at night. Light rain is expected overnight. The wind along the coast will be light. The expected UVB sunburn index will be low. The Eastern Cape is expected to be fine and cool, but partly cloudy along the coast. Isolated showers are expected. The wind along the coast will be moderate. It will be cloudy, with morning fog over the interior of KwaZulu-Natal. Rain is expected over the north. Otherwise, it will be partly cloudy and cool, but cold over the interior. The wind along the coast will be moderate. The expected UVB sunburn index will be moderate.  Click here to see the specific forecast for your city over the next few days